---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro'
import ArticleHeader from '../../components/blog/ArticleHeader.astro'
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/blog/ArticleSchema.astro'
import ArticleCTA from '../../components/blog/ArticleCTA.astro'
import ArticleBottomCTA from '../../components/blog/ArticleBottomCTA.astro'
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/blog/RelatedPosts.astro'
import { Check, MessageSquare, Bot, Users, Zap, Brain, Clock, Building2, TrendingUp, Sparkles, ArrowRight } from '@lucide/astro'
import { getPost } from '../../data/blog-posts'

const post = getPost('hotel-virtual-assistant')!

const relatedPosts = [
  {
    href: '/blog/what-is-hotel-chatbot/',
    title: 'What is a Hotel Chatbot?',
    description: 'Complete guide to hotel chatbots and how they work.'
  },
  {
    href: '/blog/guest-messaging-platform/',
    title: 'Guest Messaging Platform Guide',
    description: 'Compare messaging platforms for hotel guest communication.'
  },
  {
    href: '/blog/chatbot-for-hotels/',
    title: 'Chatbot for Hotels',
    description: 'Step-by-step implementation guide for hotel chatbots.'
  }
]
---

<Layout
  title={post.title}
  description={post.description}
  type="article"
  author={post.author.name}
  publishedTime={post.date}
>
  <ArticleSchema post={post} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a hotel virtual assistant?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A hotel virtual assistant is an AI-powered system that handles guest communication and service requests across messaging channels like WhatsApp, SMS, email, and web chat. Unlike simple chatbots that follow scripts, virtual assistants understand natural language, remember guest preferences, and can take actions like creating service requests or looking up reservation details." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How is a virtual assistant different from a hotel chatbot?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A chatbot typically follows pre-programmed scripts and keyword matching. A virtual assistant uses AI to understand context, remember past conversations, integrate with hotel systems (PMS, POS), take actions on behalf of guests, and learn from interactions. Think of a chatbot as a FAQ page that talks, and a virtual assistant as a digital concierge." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Will a virtual assistant replace my hotel staff?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. A virtual assistant handles routine inquiries (40-60% of guest messages) so your staff can focus on complex requests and personal interactions. It is a force multiplier for your existing team, not a replacement. Staff handle escalations, emotional situations, and VIP service." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does a hotel virtual assistant cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Enterprise solutions range from $200-2,000+/month depending on property size and features. Open-source self-hosted options like Jack The Butler cost $5-30/month total (hosting + AI API usage). The ROI typically comes from reduced front desk call volume, increased upsell revenue through automated offers, and measurably better guest satisfaction scores." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can a virtual assistant handle multiple languages?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. AI-powered virtual assistants can automatically detect and respond in 50+ languages without manual translation. This is one of their biggest advantages for hotels with international guests — no need for multilingual staff on every shift. The AI maintains natural, conversational tone across all supported languages." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What happens when the AI cannot answer a question?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A well-designed virtual assistant automatically escalates to human staff when it is not confident in its answer or detects an emotional situation. The guest gets a seamless handoff — the staff member sees the full conversation history and guest profile so the guest never needs to repeat themselves. Most systems also let guests request a human at any time." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does it take to set up a hotel virtual assistant?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Basic setup can be done in a day. Full implementation with knowledge base training, PMS integration, and staff onboarding typically takes 2-4 weeks. Self-hosted solutions like Jack The Butler can deploy in under 30 minutes with one-click installers." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <article class="pt-32 pb-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <ArticleHeader post={post} />

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

        <p class="lead text-xl text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
          A hotel virtual assistant is not just a <a href="/blog/what-is-hotel-chatbot/">chatbot</a> that answers FAQs. It is an AI-powered digital concierge that understands what guests need, takes action on their behalf, and gets smarter with every interaction — all while working 24/7 across every messaging channel.
        </p>

        <p>
          In this guide, we will explain how hotel virtual assistants work, what they can do that basic chatbots cannot, and how to implement one at your property without a massive technology investment.
        </p>

        <nav class="not-prose my-8 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 mb-3">Table of Contents</p>
          <ol class="columns-2 gap-x-8 text-sm space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
            <li><a href="#what-is" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">What is a Hotel Virtual Assistant?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#how-it-works" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">How It Works</a></li>
            <li><a href="#capabilities" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">What Can It Do?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#vs-chatbot" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Virtual Assistant vs Chatbot vs Live Chat</a></li>
            <li><a href="#use-cases" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Real-World Use Cases</a></li>
            <li><a href="#benefits" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Benefits for Hotels</a></li>
            <li><a href="#getting-started" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Getting Started</a></li>
            <li><a href="#faq" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">FAQ</a></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is a Hotel Virtual Assistant?</h2>

        <p>
          A hotel virtual assistant is AI software that communicates with guests through messaging channels — <a href="/blog/hotel-whatsapp-automation/">WhatsApp</a>, SMS, email, and web chat — and handles requests end-to-end. It goes beyond answering questions to actually fulfilling guest needs.
        </p>

        <p>
          When a guest messages "Can I get late checkout tomorrow?", a basic chatbot might say "Please contact the front desk." A virtual assistant checks the guest's reservation, sees the room is not booked for tomorrow, and responds "Late checkout until 2pm is available for your room. Would you like me to arrange that?"
        </p>

        <p>
          This is a fundamentally different experience. The guest gets a resolution, not a redirect. And it's important to distinguish hotel virtual assistants from voice assistants like Alexa or Siri — we are talking about messaging-based AI that integrates deeply with your hotel's operations and systems, not a smart speaker in the room.
        </p>

        <h2 id="how-it-works">How It Works</h2>

        <p>
          Behind every smooth guest interaction is a multi-step process that happens in seconds:
        </p>

      </div>

      <!-- Process Flow -->
      <div class="not-prose my-10 space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4 p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-blue-100/30 dark:from-blue-500/10 dark:to-blue-500/5 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-white font-bold text-sm" style="background-color: #3b82f6;">1</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100 mb-1">Guest Sends a Message</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200">"Is breakfast included in my booking?" via WhatsApp at 6am</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-r from-violet-50 to-violet-100/30 dark:from-violet-500/10 dark:to-violet-500/5 border border-violet-200 dark:border-violet-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-white font-bold text-sm" style="background-color: #8b5cf6;">2</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-violet-900 dark:text-violet-100 mb-1">AI Understands Intent</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-violet-800 dark:text-violet-200">Natural language processing identifies the intent (breakfast inquiry) and extracts context (guest room, booking type)</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-50 to-emerald-100/30 dark:from-emerald-500/10 dark:to-emerald-500/5 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-white font-bold text-sm" style="background-color: #10b981;">3</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900 dark:text-emerald-100 mb-1">Checks Knowledge & Data</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">Looks up the guest's reservation in the PMS and checks the hotel's knowledge base for breakfast policies and hours</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-50 to-orange-100/30 dark:from-orange-500/10 dark:to-orange-500/5 border border-orange-200 dark:border-orange-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-white font-bold text-sm" style="background-color: #f97316;">4</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-orange-900 dark:text-orange-100 mb-1">Responds or Escalates</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-orange-800 dark:text-orange-200">"Yes, breakfast is included with your Deluxe room booking! It is served in The Terrace restaurant from 7am to 10:30am." If unsure, it seamlessly hands off to staff with full context.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

        <p>
          The entire process takes seconds. At 6am, when no one is at the front desk, the guest gets a personalized, accurate answer without waking anyone up.
        </p>

        <h2 id="capabilities">What Can a Virtual Assistant Do?</h2>

        <p>
          The capabilities of a hotel virtual assistant extend far beyond answering "What time is checkout?" Here are the core areas:
        </p>

      </div>

      <!-- Capability Grid -->
      <div class="not-prose my-10 grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-blue-100/50 dark:from-blue-500/10 dark:to-blue-500/5 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-blue-500 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
            <MessageSquare class="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-2 text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100">Information & FAQs</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200">Check-in times, WiFi, parking, amenities, local recommendations, policies — drawn from your knowledge base</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-50 to-emerald-100/50 dark:from-emerald-500/10 dark:to-emerald-500/5 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-emerald-500 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
            <Zap class="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-2 text-emerald-900 dark:text-emerald-100">Service Requests</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">Extra towels, room service, housekeeping, maintenance — creates tasks and routes to the right department</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-violet-100/50 dark:from-violet-500/10 dark:to-violet-500/5 border border-violet-200 dark:border-violet-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-3" style="background-color: #8b5cf6;">
            <Users class="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-2 text-violet-900 dark:text-violet-100">Personalization</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-violet-800 dark:text-violet-200">Remembers guest preferences across stays. Knows you prefer a high floor, extra pillows, and late checkout</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-orange-100/50 dark:from-orange-500/10 dark:to-orange-500/5 border border-orange-200 dark:border-orange-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-3" style="background-color: #f97316;">
            <Building2 class="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-2 text-orange-900 dark:text-orange-100">Operations Support</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-orange-800 dark:text-orange-200">Pre-arrival messages, booking confirmations, checkout reminders, feedback collection — automated touchpoints</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-pink-100/50 dark:from-pink-500/10 dark:to-pink-500/5 border border-pink-200 dark:border-pink-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-3" style="background-color: #ec4899;">
            <TrendingUp class="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-2 text-pink-900 dark:text-pink-100">Revenue & Upselling</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-pink-800 dark:text-pink-200">Room upgrades, spa packages, dining reservations, airport transfers — personalized offers at the right moment</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-50 to-cyan-100/50 dark:from-cyan-500/10 dark:to-cyan-500/5 border border-cyan-200 dark:border-cyan-500/20">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-3" style="background-color: #06b6d4;">
            <Brain class="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-2 text-cyan-900 dark:text-cyan-100">Continuous Learning</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-cyan-800 dark:text-cyan-200">Gets smarter over time. Learns from staff corrections and new knowledge base entries to improve responses</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

        <h2 id="vs-chatbot">Virtual Assistant vs Chatbot vs Live Chat</h2>

        <p>
          These three terms get used interchangeably, but they represent very different capabilities. Understanding the differences helps you know what you actually need:
        </p>

      </div>

      <!-- Comparison Table -->
      <div class="not-prose my-12 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700">
              <th class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">Feature</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">Live Chat</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">Basic Chatbot</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">Virtual Assistant</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">Available 24/7</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Only when staff are online</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">Understands natural language</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Human does</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Keywords only</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">Multi-channel</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Web only</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Usually web only</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">WhatsApp, SMS, Email, Web</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">PMS integration</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">No</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Rare</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">Remembers guests</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">No</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">No</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">Takes actions</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Staff do</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">No</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Creates tasks, checks data</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">Staff required</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Always</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">For escalations</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">For complex issues only</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

        <p>
          The bottom line: live chat requires humans at all times. Basic chatbots handle simple keyword-matching FAQs. A virtual assistant understands context, integrates with your systems, remembers your guests, and handles most interactions end-to-end — escalating to staff only when needed.
        </p>

        <h2 id="use-cases">Real-World Use Cases</h2>

        <p>
          Here is how different types of hotels use virtual assistants in practice:
        </p>

      </div>

      <!-- Use Case Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-10 space-y-4">
        <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-blue-100/30 dark:from-blue-500/10 dark:to-blue-500/5 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-500/20">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-blue-500 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              <Building2 class="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
            </div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100">Boutique Hotel (25 rooms)</h4>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200 mb-3">
            A boutique property in Barcelona with a small staff uses a virtual assistant to handle guest messages in Spanish, English, French, and German. The AI answers 70% of inquiries automatically — mostly check-in times, restaurant recommendations, and taxi bookings.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">Result: Front desk calls dropped 45%. Staff focus on personalized guest experiences.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-50 to-emerald-100/30 dark:from-emerald-500/10 dark:to-emerald-500/5 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-500/20">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-emerald-500 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              <Sparkles class="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
            </div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900 dark:text-emerald-100">Beach Resort (150 rooms)</h4>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200 mb-3">
            A resort in Thailand uses the virtual assistant for the entire guest journey — pre-arrival upsells (spa packages, airport transfers), during-stay requests, and post-checkout feedback collection via <a href="/blog/hotel-whatsapp-automation/" class="text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300 hover:underline">WhatsApp</a>.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">Result: 20% increase in ancillary revenue from pre-arrival upsells.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-violet-100/30 dark:from-violet-500/10 dark:to-violet-500/5 border border-violet-200 dark:border-violet-500/20">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shrink-0" style="background-color: #8b5cf6;">
              <Building2 class="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
            </div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-violet-900 dark:text-violet-100">City Business Hotel (80 rooms)</h4>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-violet-800 dark:text-violet-200 mb-3">
            A business hotel in London uses the virtual assistant to handle high-volume, repetitive requests — WiFi credentials, meeting room directions, invoice requests, and taxi bookings. Business travelers value fast, no-fuss communication.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400">Result: Guest satisfaction scores increased 12%. Night shift runs with minimal staff.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

        <h2 id="benefits">Benefits for Hotels</h2>

      </div>

      <!-- Stats Box -->
      <div class="not-prose my-10 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900/50 border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="text-center p-4">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">40-60%</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">Reduction in routine front desk inquiries</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">24/7</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">Availability without additional night staff</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400">15-25%</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">Increase in ancillary revenue from automated upsells</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400">50+</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">Languages supported automatically by AI</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

        <p>
          The benefits compound over time. As the virtual assistant learns your property's patterns and builds guest profiles, responses become more accurate and personalized. Hotels that run a virtual assistant for 6+ months consistently see higher automation rates than in month one.
        </p>

        <p>
          The scalability advantage is particularly important. A human concierge can handle one conversation at a time. A virtual assistant handles hundreds simultaneously. During peak check-in, when the front desk is busiest, the AI absorbs the messaging load so staff can focus on the guests standing in front of them.
        </p>

      </div>

      <ArticleCTA />

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

        <h2 id="getting-started">Getting Started</h2>

        <p>
          Implementing a hotel virtual assistant is more straightforward than you might think. Here is a practical 6-step approach:
        </p>

      </div>

      <!-- Step Boxes -->
      <div class="not-prose my-10 space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4 p-5 rounded-2xl bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-500/20">
